ingdom of Romania]] in 1881.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Hellenic Kingdom Flag 1935.svg}} [[Kingdom of Greece]]\n| {{flagicon image|Hellenic Kingdom Flag 1935.svg}} [[Kingdom of Greece]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the United States of the Ionian Islands.svg}} [[United States of the Ionian Islands]]\n| 1864\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| [[Treaty of London (1864)]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the German Empire.svg}} [[North German Confederation]]\n| {{flag|Prussia|name=Kingdom of Prussia}}<br />{{flag|Kingdom of Saxony}}<br />{{flag|Grand Duchy of Hesse}}<br />{{flag|Mecklenburg-Schwerin|name=Mecklenburg-Schwerin}}<br />{{flag|Mecklenburg-Strelitz|name=Grand Duchy of Mecklenburg-Strelitz}}<br />{{flag|Oldenburg|name=Grand Duchy of Oldenburg}}<br />{{flag|Saxe-Weimar-Eisenach|name=Duchy of Saxe-Weimar-Eisenach}}<br />{{flag|Anhalt|name=Duchy of Anhalt}}<br />{{flag|Duchy of Brunswick}}<br />{{flag|Saxe-Altenburg|name=Duchy of Saxe-Altenburg}}<br />{{flag|Saxe-Coburg-Gotha}}<br />{{flag|Saxe-Meiningen|name=Duchy of Saxe-Meiningen}}<br />Various other small principalities and free cities\n| 1866\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1867\u20131871)}}\n| Following the [[Austro-Prussian War]] of 1866 and the annexation by Prussia of Austria's northern German ally states, [[Otto von Bismarck]] proposed to unify Prussia and its own German ally states into a single Federation. Consequently, the [[North German Constitution]] was adopted, with the provision that the southern German minor states could enter into the union when politically feasible.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Canadian Red Ensign 1868-1921.svg}} [[Canada]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the United Kingdom.svg}} [[Province of Canada]]<br />{{flag|New Brunswick|colony}}<br />{{flag|Nova Scotia}}\n| 1867\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Canadian Confederation]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Lares (1868).svg}} [[Antillean Confederation]]\n| {{flagicon image|Naval Jack of Cuba.svg}} [[Captaincy General of Cuba]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Lares (1868).svg}} [[Captaincy General of Puerto Rico]]<br />{{flag|Dominican Republic}}\n| 1869\u20131870\n| {{no}}\n| Proposed by [[Ram\u00f3n Emeterio Betances]].\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the German Empire.svg}} [[German Empire]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the German Empire.svg}} [[North German Confederation]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Bavaria (striped).svg}} [[Kingdom of Bavaria]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flagge K\u00f6nigreich W\u00fcrttemberg.svg}} [[Kingdom of W\u00fcrttemberg]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flagge Gro\u00dfherzogtum Baden (1891-1918).svg}} [[Grand Duchy of Baden]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flagge Gro\u00dfherzogtum Hessen ohne Wappen.svg}} [[Grand Duchy of Hesse]]<br />{{flagicon image|Dienstflagge Elsa\u00df-Lothringen Kaiserreich.svg}} [[Alsace-Lorraine]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Habsburg Monarchy.svg}} [[Austrian Empire]]\n| 1871\n| {{yes|Partial <br /> (1871\u20131918)}}\n| [[Unification of Germany]] (excluding Austria) after German victory over the French in the [[Franco-Prussian War]]. See also, the [[German Question]] regarding the competing ideas of \"Greater Germany\" and \"Lesser Germany\" (whether or not a united Germany should include the Austrian Empire). The matter was settled with the [[Austro-Prussian War]] in 1866, in which Prussia assumed leadership of the various minor German nation states.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Bulgaria.svg}} [[Principality of Bulgaria]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Bulgaria.svg}} [[Bulgaria]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Eastern Rumelia.svg}} [[East Rumelia]]\n| 1885-1886\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| After Bulgaria crushed Serbia in the [[Serbo-Bulgarian War]] of 1885, Bulgaria nearly doubled in size when [[East Rumelia]] was incorporated within its borders. Bulgaria officially annexed it from the [[Ottoman Empire]] in 1885.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Zentralamerikanische Gro\u00dfrepublik 1898.svg}} [[Greater Republic of Central America]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of El Salvador (1875-1877).svg}} [[El Salvador]]<br />{{flagi