ia into accepting integration into Yugoslavia, but relations cooled in 1948 over fears that Yugoslavia only intended to use Albania for raw materials, subsequently resulting in the expulsion of Yugoslav diplomats. Yugoslav/Bulgarian negotiations fell through when Moscow attempted to force both countries into accepting Soviet control over the merge, which caused Yugoslavia to withdraw from negotiations and precipitated the [[Tito\u2013Stalin split]].\n|-\n| {{flag|India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon image|Drapeau Junagadh vector.svg}} [[Junagadh State|Junagadh]]\n| 1947\u20131948\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Annexation of Junagadh]]\n|-\n| {{flag|India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon|British Raj}}[[List of princely states of British India (alphabetical)|Princely states]]\n| 1947\u20131950\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Instrument of Accession]]\n|-\n| {{flag|Pakistan}}\n| {{flag|Pakistan}}<br />[[List of princely states of British India (alphabetical)|Princely states]]\n| 1947\u20131950\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Instrument of Accession]]\n|-\n| {{flag|India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon image|Asafia flag of Hyderabad State.png}} [[Hyderabad State|Hyderabad]]\n| 1948\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Indian annexation of Hyderabad|Annexation of Hyderabad]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Canadian Red Ensign 1921-1957.svg}} [[Canada]]\n| {{flagicon image|Canadian Red Ensign 1921-1957.svg}} [[Canada]]<br />{{flagicon image|Dominion of Newfoundland Red Ensign.svg}} [[Dominion of Newfoundland|Newfoundland]]\n| 1949\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| [[Newfoundland Act]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland (1953\u20131963).svg}} [[Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland]]\n| {{flag|Nyasaland|1963}}<br />{{flag|Northern Rhodesia|1939-1953}}<br />{{flag|Southern Rhodesia}}\n| 1953\n| {{yes|Yes <br />(1953\u20131963)}}\n| A semi-independent state.\n|-\n| {{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[United Kingdom]]\n| {{flag|United Kingdom}}<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Malta (1943-1964).svg}} [[Crown Colony of Malta]]\